<subSubSection id="0FBA4DDBAA49A7211C994FBF8E5C5202" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="host">
<paragraph id="4D0900B1FEBDD98E2994D19E6B62233D" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Hosts.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="825DED47D89AF660C29F2C5588410437" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
More than seven insect orders, including 
<taxonomicName id="ED4FA74BE9ADA54F07FB71DDFE9E9DF6" authorityName="Sorokin" authorityYear="1879" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Clavicipitaceae" genus="Metarhizium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="order">Coleoptera</taxonomicName>
(e.g. 
<taxonomicName id="C0CC66388FA8B1060767B1CCCC77B3CC" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="? arthropoda" rank="family">Elateridae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="3D5178B732E2499810EDA1D144875402" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" class="Hexapoda" family="Tenebrionidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Tenebrionidae</taxonomicName>
spp., 
<bibRefCitation id="BB93BC2E6FBCFF21EF273BD576834545" author="Kabaluk, T" journalOrPublisher="IOBC / WPRS Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="109 - 115" refId="B28" refString="Kabaluk, T, Goettel, M, Erlandson, M, Ericsson, J, Duke, G, Vernon, B, 2005. Metarhizium anisopliae as a biological control for wireworms and a report of some other naturally-occurring parasites. IOBC/WPRS Bulletin 28: 109 - 115" title="Metarhizium anisopliae as a biological control for wireworms and a report of some other naturally-occurring parasites." volume="28" year="2005">Kabaluk et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="1C342171826E5B7E705684DA561DF534" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jip.2017.09.012" author="Kabaluk, T" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Invertebrate Pathology" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="82 - 87" refId="B29" refString="Kabaluk, T, Li-Leger, E, Nam, S, 2017. Metarhizium brunneum - an enzootic wireworm disease and evidence for its suppression by bacterial symbionts. Journal of Invertebrate Pathology 150: 82 - 87, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jip.2017.09.012" title="Metarhizium brunneum - an enzootic wireworm disease and evidence for its suppression by bacterial symbionts." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jip.2017.09.012" volume="150" year="2017">2017</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="CF7B2BBB81697863E35789DC7292FCE1" author="Humber, RA" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences, USA" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" publicationUrl="http://arsef.fpsnl.cornell.edu./" refId="B20" refString="Humber, RA, Hansen, KS, 2005. USDA-ARS Collection of Entomopathogenic Fungal Cultures (ARSEF), ARSEF-Index: Host by Fungus. http://arsef.fpsnl.cornell.edu./" title="USDA-ARS Collection of Entomopathogenic Fungal Cultures (ARSEF), ARSEF-Index: Host by Fungus." url="http://arsef.fpsnl.cornell.edu./" year="2005">Humber and Hansen 2005</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="C8ACA8A31CE3EFAFC3D9646216C18DFA" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jip.2014.05.005" author="Reddy, GVP" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Invertebrate Pathology" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="43 - 49" refId="B70" refString="Reddy, GVP, Tangtrakulwanich, K, Wu, SH, Miller, JH, Ophus, VL, Prewett, J, Jaronski, ST, 2014. Evaluation of the effectiveness of entomopathogens for the management of wireworms (Coleoptera: Elateridae) on spring wheat. Journal of Invertebrate Pathology 120: 43 - 49, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jip.2014.05.005" title="Evaluation of the effectiveness of entomopathogens for the management of wireworms (Coleoptera: Elateridae) on spring wheat." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jip.2014.05.005" volume="120" year="2014">Reddy et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
); inhabiting soil, plant surfaces and plant internal tissues (
<bibRefCitation id="9017BCB138DA452E0067E6B6BC31F02F" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1073/pnas.1412662111" author="Hu, X" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences, USA" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="16796 - 16801" refId="B19" refString="Hu, X, Xiao, G, Zheng, P, Shang, Y, Su, Y, Zhang, X, Liu, X, Zhan, S, St Leger, RJ, Wang, C, 2014. Trajectory and genomic determinants of fungal-pathogen speciation and host adaptation. Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences, USA 111: 16796 - 16801, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1073/pnas.1412662111" title="Trajectory and genomic determinants of fungal-pathogen speciation and host adaptation." url="https://doi.org/10.1073/pnas.1412662111" volume="111" year="2014">Hu et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="3CCE3DE7957780B8840E46CB1D33F637" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.micres.2018.08.016" author="Bamisile, BS" journalOrPublisher="Microbiological Research" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="34 - 50" refId="B2" refString="Bamisile, BS, Dash, CK, Akutse, KS, Keppanan, R, Afolabi, OG, Hussain, M, Qasim, M, Wang, L, 2018. Prospects of endophytic fungal entomopathogens as biocontrol and plant growth promoting agents: an insight on how artificial inoculation methods affect endophytic colonization of host plants. Microbiological Research 217: 34 - 50, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.micres.2018.08.016" title="Prospects of endophytic fungal entomopathogens as biocontrol and plant growth promoting agents: an insight on how artificial inoculation methods affect endophytic colonization of host plants." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.micres.2018.08.016" volume="217" year="2018">Bamisile et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="002F78D2BEE454B98CD205BD789B5530" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/09583157.2018.1531111" author="Brunner-Mendoza, C" journalOrPublisher="Biocontrol Science and Technology" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="83 - 102" refId="B7" refString="Brunner-Mendoza, C, Reyes-Montes, MDR, Moonjely, S, Bidochka, MJ, Toriello, C, 2019. A review on the genus Metarhizium as an entomopathogenic microbial biocontrol agent with emphasis on its use and utility in Mexico. Biocontrol Science and Technology 29 (1): 83 - 102, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/09583157.2018.1531111" title="A review on the genus Metarhizium as an entomopathogenic microbial biocontrol agent with emphasis on its use and utility in Mexico." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/09583157.2018.1531111" volume="29" year="2019">Brunner-Mendoza et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CFD1FF93F9E1B0FD619A0EE27F7E92FC" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="0883F36E7AB7F4EDEC6EAEAE41AC875E" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BB6FF2B894516FAAB82C0ED991CB5ADC" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Widely distributed.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B4A3764EB58F7FABD31B5A91C65685B6" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="notes">
<paragraph id="306FF2D4FB296ECC21F88A9B70EB9077" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A3778375D4AE1AFBC1591EB7A18E3EF2" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
<taxonomicName id="DC6188B64297313A0BBA92CE10C3A0F4" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Clavicipitaceae" genus="Metarhizium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Metarhizium anisopliae" order="Hypocreales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="anisopliae">
<emphasis id="EF5D3CE0BB7696DF2D9FB6B08FEF5DA8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Metarhizium anisopliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species complex includes several cryptic species, for example, 
<taxonomicName id="DBCA881F19670E406C9F5F3FB89DADA9" genus="M." lsidName="M. anisopliae" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="anisopliae">
<emphasis id="1538339A90351F87A741AE95F7B49A89" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">M. anisopliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Metschn.) 
<normalizedToken id="4396266140A993539CF7B56D49B49AA6" originalValue="Sorokīn">Sorokīn</normalizedToken>
, 
<taxonomicName id="5F9B9A8697FD3B5A55C3FCF951CCBE61" genus="M." lsidName="M. brunneum" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="brunneum">
<emphasis id="7C44997904BF752009344628C066271D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">M. brunneum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Petch and 
<taxonomicName id="196B43272C3B2CD413D2A059CBDC95FD" genus="M." lsidName="M. robertsii" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="robertsii">
<emphasis id="7CA502850D42EA293148DA148CBF97FB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">M. robertsii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
J.F. Bisch., S.A. Rehner &amp; Humber (
<bibRefCitation id="B6A80F5025F0F9C2A85E66D440157301" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3852/07-202" author="Bischoff, JF" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="512 - 530" refId="B6" refString="Bischoff, JF, Rehner, SA, Humber, RA, 2009. A multilocus phylogeny of the Metarhizium anisopliae lineage. Mycologia 101 (4): 512 - 530, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3852/07-202" title="A multilocus phylogeny of the Metarhizium anisopliae lineage." url="https://doi.org/10.3852/07-202" volume="101" year="2009">Bischoff et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="E52D26DDCA37B3929BC3E4FEBB66593C" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3852/13-319" author="Kepler, RM" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="811 - 829" refId="B33" refString="Kepler, RM, Humber, RA, Bischoff, JF, Rehner, SA, 2014. Clarification of generic and species boundaries for Metarhizium and related fungi through multigene phylogenetics. Mycologia 106 (4): 811 - 829, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3852/13-319" title="Clarification of generic and species boundaries for Metarhizium and related fungi through multigene phylogenetics." url="https://doi.org/10.3852/13-319" volume="106" year="2014">Kepler et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="50F08A53284791FF76C0864E2AD693E7" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.simyco.2020.04.001" author="Mongkolsamrit, S" journalOrPublisher="Studies in Mycology" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="171 - 251" refId="B61" refString="Mongkolsamrit, S, Khonsanit, A, Thanakitpipattana, D, Tasanathai, K, Noisripoom, W, Lamlertthon, S, Himaman, W, Houbraken, J, Samson, RA, Luangsa-ard, J, 2020. Revisiting Metarhizium and the description of new species from Thailand. Studies in Mycology 95: 171 - 251, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.simyco.2020.04.001" title="Revisiting Metarhizium and the description of new species from Thailand." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.simyco.2020.04.001" volume="95" year="2020">Mongkolsamrit et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
). Amongst them, 
<taxonomicName id="1AFD3D174A1AA65BACC60063148E8E99" genus="M." lsidName="M. brunneum" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="brunneum">
<emphasis id="00D51BCA37DB43029CED73A69463D8E7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">M. brunneum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was most often noted as a wireworm pathogen (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="AA844FC8124A03A3756009D05556E693" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jip.2017.09.012" author="Kabaluk, T" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Invertebrate Pathology" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="82 - 87" refId="B29" refString="Kabaluk, T, Li-Leger, E, Nam, S, 2017. Metarhizium brunneum - an enzootic wireworm disease and evidence for its suppression by bacterial symbionts. Journal of Invertebrate Pathology 150: 82 - 87, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jip.2017.09.012" title="Metarhizium brunneum - an enzootic wireworm disease and evidence for its suppression by bacterial symbionts." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jip.2017.09.012" volume="150" year="2017">Kabaluk et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
